new.name: CVE-2024-8856
new.description: This tool scans WordPress websites for vulnerabilities in the WP Time Capsule plugin related to CVE-2024-8856. It identifies plugin versions below 1.22.22 as vulnerable and logs results to vuln.txt. Simple and efficient, it helps security researchers and admins detect and address risks quickly.

new.name: CVE-2024-10508
new.description: This tool scans WordPress sites for vulnerabilities in the "RegistrationMagic" plugin (CVE-2024-10508). It checks for the presence of a specific version (`6.0.2.6`) and marks the site as vulnerable if found. The results are saved in a file (`vuln.txt`) for further analysis.
